Package frechetDistance

Class FrechetDeciderPath

java.lang.Object
frechetDistance.FrechetDecider
frechetDistance.FrechetDeciderPath
public class FrechetDeciderPath
extends FrechetDecider
A decider for the fréchet decision problem using a path finding approach.

The decision problem is the question whether the fréchet distance of two polygons is less or equal a given distance. This implementation of a FrechetDecider uses my path finding approach.

For that the free space and reachability is only calculated for a cell if necessary. This is generally faster than FrechetDeciderTabular.

Author:
Anton Ballmaier

    • prioritize

      private java.util.List<ReachableCell> prioritize​(ReachableCell right, ReachableCell up, ReachableCell diagonal)
      Sorts the given ReachableCells in ascending priority. Only actual ReachableCells will be included in the List, null values are being dropped.

      If present the diagonal ReachableCell always has the highest priority. Of the other two cells the one closer to the diagonal of the free space diagram has higher priority.

      Parameters:
      right - the right cell relative to the current
      up - the top cell relative to the current
      diagonal - the diagonal cell relative to the current
      Returns:
      the list of the non-null cells in ascending priority

    • stepDiagonal

      private ReachableCell stepDiagonal​(ReachableCell current)
      Tries to take a diagonal step from the current cell and returns the reached cell of possible.

      The following cases will result in returning null however:

      • stepping diagonal would result in leaving the free space diagram
      • the top right corner of the current cell is not within it's free space
      • the diagonal cell has already been visited without restriction
      If the cell was already visited with a restriction the same ReachableCell object created before will be returned with updated restriction.
      Parameters:
      current - the current cell
      Returns:
      the diagonal cell or null

    • stepRight

      private ReachableCell stepRight​(ReachableCell current)
      Tries to take a step right from the current cell and returns the reached cell of possible.

      The following cases will result in returning null however:

      • stepping right would result in leaving the free space diagram
      • the current cell has no right free interval
      • the right cell can't be reached due to the current restriction
      • the right cell has already been visited with same or less significant restriction
      If the cell was already visited with a more significant restriction the same ReachableCell object created before will be returned with updated restriction.
      Parameters:
      current - the current cell
      Returns:
      the right cell or null

    • stepUp

      If the cell was already visited with a more significant restriction the same ReachableCell object created before will be returned with updated restriction.
